  "five_kzm_class_status": "Five KZM-density classes have fixed proportional ratios (1.00, 1.23, 1.41, 1.73, 2.00) approximately sqrt(1, 1.5, 2, 3, 4) across all 9 regimes; they are NOT 5 independent fermion families but graduated quench-rate / threshold levels of one underlying KZM-defect statistic. All 5 classes correlate identically with diagonal-block T_munu.",
  "headline": "Vortex-background decomposition extracts a vortex-density-independent background at w_bg = -0.3347 (within 0.4% of SEC saturation -1/3) plus a per-vortex modulation at w_pv = -0.7804 (phantom-like). The Phase G/L/M anisotropy headline reads structurally as vortex-defect-network background + finite-density modulation, consistent with cosmic-string-network / domain-wall / k/a^2 spatial-curvature equation-of-state classes.",
